 the Z$_2$ topology of the spin-orbit band\nstructure and opposite parity band inversions, which led to the experimental\ndiscovery of the first 3D topological insulators. We also discuss how\nspectroscopic methods are leading to the identification of spin-orbit\nsuperconductors that may work as Majorana platforms and can be used to identify\ntopological superconductors - yet another class of new state of matter.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 2 May 2011 18:17:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-05-03"}
