ich is high for relaxed, high-mass clusters, but\nconsistent with LCDM when a sizable projection bias estimated from N-body\nsimulations is considered. This possible tension will be more definitively\nexplored with new cluster surveys, such as CLASH, LoCuSS, Subaru HSC, and\nXXM-XXL, to construct the c-M relation over a wider mass range.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 2 May 2011 21:50:25 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 11 Jun 2011 10:48:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-28"}
