y of a uniformly accelerated object. Every rest point of K' is\nuniformly accelerated, and its acceleration is a function of the observer's\nacceleration and its position. We obtain an interpretation of the\nLorentz-Abraham-Dirac equation as an acceleration transformation from K' to K.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 3 May 2011 07:08:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 3 Oct 2011 10:47:20 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 29 Apr 2013 09:32:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-04-30"}
